<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="32" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
Species of this genus breed only in the flowers of grasses and are readily recognized from the shape of the head, pronotum, fore legs and antennae. This genus includes 53 species in the world (
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="32">ThripsWiki 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Six species in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Chirothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chirothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chirothrips</taxonomicName>
and two species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hood, 1954" authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Agrostothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Agrostothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrostothrips</taxonomicName>
Hood have been reported from Iran (
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Bhatti et al. 2009a</bibRefCitation>
) but subsquentley 
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei, K" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="33 - 43" title="Grass-flower thrips of the genus Chirothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae), with a key to species from Iran." volume="2411" year="2010">Minaei and Mound (2010)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Hood, 1954" authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Agrostothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Agrostothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrostothrips</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Chirothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chirothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chirothrips</taxonomicName>
and five species and one species-group (manicatus group) have been recognized in this country. A key also to the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Chirothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chirothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chirothrips</taxonomicName>
species from Iran was given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei, K" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="33 - 43" title="Grass-flower thrips of the genus Chirothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae), with a key to species from Iran." volume="2411" year="2010">Minaei and Mound (2010)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
